Package uk.knightz.knightzapi.menu.adapter.token

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Token<O>
    Any Token
    Token.DataToken<O,V>
    An extension of Token for MethodToken and FieldToken
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FieldAttributes<T>
    A serializable, thread-safe store of some of the attributes of a certain Field object It does not store a reference to the original Field, as this poses a security risk when serializing It also doesn't store the return type of the Field because when stored in a Field token, the return type can be obtained with Token.DataToken.getValue() Object.getClass()
    FieldToken<V>
    Token that stores attributes about a Field, and a value of that field
    MethodAttributes<T>
    A serializable, thread-safe store of some of the attributes of a certain Method object It does not store a reference to the original Method, as this poses a security risk when serializing It also doesn't store the return type of the Method because when stored in a Method token, the return type can be obtained with Token.DataToken.getValue() Object.getClass()
    MethodToken<V>
    Token that stores attributes about a Method, and a value of that Method
    ObjectToken<T>
    Data class to represent the field structure and values of an object in a serializing friendly way An example data class: { name: "Steve", age: 27 } would be converted to an ObjectToken looking like this: { tokens: [ FieldToken<String> { name.field,"Steve" }, FieldToken<Integer> { age.field, 27 } ] }
    PrimitiveToken<T>
    A subclass of ObjectToken to represent a primitive type.
    Tokenizer
    Converts Methods and Fields into Tokens
